[1] Case updates
- Tue 8 Jan 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=30f733dd94

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 7 Jan 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 627, of which 579 are confirmed and 48 are probable. In total, there were 382 deaths (334 confirmed and 48 probable) and 221 people recovered.
- 98 suspected cases under investigation.
- 2 new confirmed cases, including 1 in Oicha and 1 in Katwa.
- 5 new deaths of confirmed cases, including 3 in Butembo, 1 in Beni, and 1 in Katwa (1 community death).
- 1 new recovery released from Butembo ETC.

News of the response
Vaccination
-----------
- Since the beginning of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 56 866 [corrected number from MoH] people have been vaccinated, including 19 619 in Beni [North Kivu], 11 526 in Katwa [North Kivu], 6476 in Butembo [North Kivu], 5550 in Mabalako [North Kivu], 2283 in Kalunguta [North Kivu], 1684 in Komanda [Ituri], 1663 in Mandima [Ituri], 1222 in Oicha [North Kivu], 1166 in Goma [North Kivu], 791 in Vuhovi [North Kivu], 750 in Masereka [North Kivu], 719 in Kyondo [North Kivu], 700 in Lubero [North Kivu], 599 in Mutwanga [North Kivu], 558 in Karisimbi [North Kivu], 434 in Bunia [Ituri], 394 in Musienene [North Kivu], 355 in Tchomia [Ituri], 167 in Nyankunde [North Kivu], 70 in Biena [North Kivu], 63 in Alimbongo [North Kivu], 54 in Nyiragongo [North Kivu], and 13 in Kisangani [Tshopo].

The only vaccine to be used in this outbreak is the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, following approval by the Ethics Committee in its decision of 19 May 2018.

