- Mon 7 Jan 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=7af14fa080

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 6 Jan 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 625, of which 577 are confirmed and 48 are probable. In total, there were 377 deaths (329 confirmed and 48 probable) and 220 people recovered*.
- 101 suspected cases under investigation.
- 2 new confirmed cases, including 1 in Mabalako and 1 in Katwa.
- 3 new deaths of confirmed cases, 2 in Katwa (1 community death) and 1 in Butembo.
- 4 new recoveries, including 3 releases from the Mangina ETC and 1 from the Butembo ETC.

News of the response
Vaccination
-----------
- Since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 56 509 people have been vaccinated [total numbers of people vaccinated in North Kivu, Ituri, and Tshopo provinces can be seen at the source URL above].

