- Sun 6 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=fd4d70a646

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 5 Jan 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 623, of which 575 are confirmed and 48 are probable. In total, there were 374 deaths (326 confirmed and 48 probable) and 216 people recovered*.
- 122 suspect cases under investigation.
- 9 new confirmed cases, including 4 in Butembo, 2 in Oicha, 1 in Katwa, 1 in Kyondo, and 1 in Kalunguta.
- No deaths of confirmed cases reported today.
- 2 new recoveries released from Butembo ETC.
*Reclassification of cases and deaths by health zone after update of the database.

News of the response
Vaccination
-----------
- Immunization launched for front-line providers in Nyiragongo Health Zone, Goma city [North Kivu].
- Since the beginning of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 56 211 people have been vaccinated [total numbers of people vaccinated in North Kivu, Ituri, and Tshopo provinces can be seen at the source URL above].

